### Chapa Payment Integration Tests
### Use with VS Code REST Client extension or similar

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@token = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
@bookingId = YOUR_BOOKING_ID_HERE
@txRef = booking-xxx-timestamp

### 1. Login to get JWT token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@hotel.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### 2. Create a test booking first
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "roomId": "YOUR_ROOM_ID_HERE",
  "guestName": "John Doe",
  "guestPhone": "+251911223344",
  "checkIn": "2026-07-15",
  "checkOut": "2026-07-17"
}

### 3. Initialize Chapa payment for the booking
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/payments/bookings/{{bookingId}}/initiate-payment
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "returnUrl": "http://localhost:5173/payment-success"
}

### Response should include:
### - checkoutUrl: Redirect guest here
### - txRef: Transaction reference
### - bookingId: Booking ID

### 4. Simulate Chapa webhook (successful payment)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/payments/webhook
Content-Type: application/json
x-chapa-signature: CALCULATE_HMAC_SHA256_SIGNATURE_HERE

{
  "event": "charge.success",
  "first_name": "John",
  "last_name": "Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "mobile": "0911223344",
  "currency": "ETB",
  "amount": "2400.00",
  "charge": "72.00",
  "status": "success",
  "mode": "test",
  "reference": "APqDvYw1okk2",
  "created_at": "2026-07-02T10:30:00.000000Z",
  "updated_at": "2026-07-02T10:30:10.000000Z",
  "type": "API",
  "tx_ref": "{{txRef}}",
  "payment_method": "telebirr",
  "customization": {
    "title": "Hotel Booking Payment",
    "description": "Payment for Room 101 - John Doe",
    "logo": null
  },
  "meta": null
}

### 5. Simulate Chapa webhook (failed payment)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/payments/webhook
Content-Type: application/json
x-chapa-signature: CALCULATE_HMAC_SHA256_SIGNATURE_HERE

{
  "event": "charge.failed",
  "status": "failed",
  "tx_ref": "{{txRef}}",
  "type": "API"
}

### 6. Verify payment manually
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/payments/verify/{{txRef}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 7. Get booking to check payment status
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/bookings
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Expected paymentStatus values:
### - "pending" - Payment not yet initiated
### - "paid" - Payment successful
### - "failed" - Payment failed or cancelled

### 8. Test with invalid webhook signature (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/payments/webhook
Content-Type: application/json
x-chapa-signature: invalid-signature-here

{
  "event": "charge.success",
  "tx_ref": "{{txRef}}",
  "status": "success"
}

### Expected: 401 Unauthorized or webhook ignored

### Notes:
### - Replace {{token}}, {{bookingId}}, {{txRef}} with actual values
### - For webhook signature: Use HMAC SHA256 with CHAPA_WEBHOOK_SECRET
### - In test mode, use test cards on Chapa checkout page
### - Check console logs for payment flow details
